## Guidelines for GIFs
- Keep file size under 5MB each
- Duration: 5-10 seconds
- Frame rate: 15-20 FPS
- Show key user interactions
- Include smooth transitions

## Recommended Tools
- LICEcap (cross-platform)
- GIPHY Capture (Mac)
- ScreenToGif (Windows)
- ffmpeg for optimization

## Optimization Commands
```bash
# Optimize GIF size
ffmpeg -i input.gif -vf "fps=15,scale=320:-1:flags=lanczos" -c:v gif output.gif

# Convert video to optimized GIF
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vf "fps=20,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos,palettegen" palette.png
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -i palette.png -vf "fps=20,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos,paletteuse" output.gif
```
